Use of AI in This Project (Olena)

AI was used as a support tool to assist with content creation, design decisions, and technical implementation. 
I used AI to generate destination descriptions and activity ideas, which I reviewed and adjusted to fit the theme and style of my website.

AI also helped improve the UI/UX design, including text overlay on images, better positioning, 
spacing, and selecting colors to improve readability and create a more professional travel website look.

For the technical part, AI assisted with CSS and responsive design, including the use of flexbox, grid, clamp() for responsive text, 
and media queries to adapt the layout for different screen sizes. It also helped implement styling techniques such as pseudo-elements (::before), which were used to create overlays on images to improve text visibility without adding extra HTML elements.

Additionally, AI supported problem-solving and debugging, helping me understand and fix issues in HTML and CSS, including layout alignment and positioning.

Examples of AI Prompts Used

“Create short descriptions for BC destinations for a travel website”

“How to make text stand out on an image using CSS overlay”

“How to create a responsive card layout using flexbox or grid”

“How to use media queries for responsive design”

“How to use ::before for image overlay in CSS”

All final decisions, edits, and implementation were completed by me, and I ensured I understood how the code works.
